                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490820-name-1155" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1155" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1155" type="surname" value="DODGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1155" type="given" value="ESAU"></interp>ESAU DODGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Wellington-place, Blackfriars, On 10th Aug. the prisoner came, and spoke about buying a horse—he left some time after, and I missed a screw-wrench—I sent my servant after him—he refused to return—I have no doubt that he is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490820-name-1156" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1156" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1156" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490820-name-1156" type="given" value="NATHAN"></interp>NATHAN HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the prosecutor's service. On 10th Aug., about ten minutes before four o'clock, the prisoner came—I was up in the loft—I saw him go to the <hi rend="italic">cab</hi>, and take out a screw-wrench which I had put there—he called out for Mr. George, and asked him if he wanted to buy a horse—I saw him go away with the wrench.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> How was I dressed? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> You had a light drab coat and a cap on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had a hat on from three o'clock till five that day; I was at the Tom Thumb, in the New-cut; there was a sale there.</p>
